<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>4347</id>
    <title>People: Viewer on a private site can't be invited as a member of the site</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Expected behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">If a user is a Viewer on a private site, it should be possible to invite them to become a member (Contributor, Author, Editor, or Administrator) on the same site.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">This is possible in Calypso web.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">If a user is a Viewer on a private site, and you try to invite them as a Viewer again, Calypso shows an error:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">[screen shot 2016-07-04 at 5 51 02 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8658164/16566830/071a7be2-4210-11e6-82e7-1320012ed81b.png)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">But if you select a different role for that Viewer, the invite works:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">[screen shot 2016-07-04 at 5 51 11 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8658164/16566844/23f849ce-4210-11e6-97b2-fa2dbdd572e6.png)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">### Actual behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">If a user is a Viewer on a private site, you are blocked from inviting them to become a member (Contributor, Author, Editor, or Administrator) on the same site.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">[2016-07-04 16 40 25](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8658164/16566864/5ad9dcb4-4210-11e6-82fd-07cd581fe991.png)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.2">1 Select a private site and add a user as a Viewer on that site</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.3">2 In the app, go to the site dashboard &gt; People and tap the plus icon to invite a new member</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.4">3 Enter the username or email of the Viewer on the site</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.5">4 Tap in another field or tap Send</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">Result: An error appears in red: "There's already a member with the username 'USERNAME'"
##### Tested on Nexus 9, Android 6.0.1, WPAndroid alpha-16</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
